1
00:00:04,159 --> 00:00:08,027
-And now the NCAA Final Four
Post Game Show.

2
00:00:08,892 --> 00:00:10,399
-Thank you so much.

3
00:00:10,399 --> 00:00:14,332
Welcome back
to the Post Game Show
sponsored by Capital One.

4
00:00:14,332 --> 00:00:18,523
We hope you enjoyed
that commercial
where Spike Lee,
Samuel L. Jackson,

5
00:00:18,523 --> 00:00:21,034
and Jennifer Garner
are supposed to be friends.

6
00:00:21,034 --> 00:00:24,536
I'm Ernie Johnson here
with Kenny "The Jet" Smith,

7
00:00:24,536 --> 00:00:26,612
Sir Charles Barkley...

8
00:00:26,612 --> 00:00:29,227
and coach Bruce Pearl.

9
00:00:29,227 --> 00:00:32,548
Well, fellas, let's-- let's talk
about tonight's first game

10
00:00:32,548 --> 00:00:36,484
where Connecticut
beat Illinois, 71-62.

11
00:00:36,484 --> 00:00:39,264
Bad night
for Illinois' offense!

12
00:00:39,256 --> 00:00:42,560
-Indeed.
They got shut down faster
than an 11-year-old

13
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:45,283
asking
for Chappell Roan's autograph.

14
00:00:45,283 --> 00:00:48,648
-Yeah, Ernie, man,
that game was miraculous.

15
00:00:48,648 --> 00:00:53,736
It was spectacular.
I mean, one could
call it miraca-tacular.

16
00:00:53,736 --> 00:00:57,705
-Absolutely.
It was almost as impressive
as when Chuck

17
00:00:57,705 --> 00:01:01,051
spoke
so eloquently about immigrants
last week.

18
00:01:01,051 --> 00:01:02,937
-Oh, well,
thank you very much.

19
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:05,953
-That's right. That's right.
That's right, Chuckster.

20
00:01:05,953 --> 00:01:10,460
Now, you got a lot of love
for your passionate defense
of the immigrant experience
on this very show.

21
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,576
-Oh, well,
I got to tell you, man,
all kind of people
were texting me, e-mailing me.

22
00:01:14,576 --> 00:01:18,915
It's the first time I went viral
without a prescription
for Valtrex.

23
00:01:18,915 --> 00:01:22,951
-People love
sincere Charles Barkley.

24
00:01:22,951 --> 00:01:26,400
-They do, right?!
It's crazy, man!

25
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:29,586
-Alright, well, let's move on
to the highlights from tonight.

26
00:01:29,586 --> 00:01:33,417
-Oh, before we do, Ernie,
can I say something?
-Oh, uh, s-sure.

27
00:01:33,417 --> 00:01:37,963
-Now, this might get me fired,
so I'm gonna choose my words
real careful right now.

28
00:01:37,963 --> 00:01:42,017
Look, there's a war going on
between us and Iran.

29
00:01:42,017 --> 00:01:45,259
Um, war-- war is turrible.

30
00:01:45,259 --> 00:01:47,468
Um, innocent people
getting killed.

31
00:01:47,468 --> 00:01:50,692
And I don't care who started it,
but we need to end it, okay?

32
00:01:50,692 --> 00:01:53,318
-Hey, man,
I appreciate that, Chuck.

33
00:01:53,318 --> 00:01:55,015
-Uh, thank you, Charles.

34
00:01:55,015 --> 00:01:58,725
Let's-- Let's talk about
the late game
where Michigan beat Arizona.

35
00:01:58,725 --> 00:02:02,224
Coach Pearl, any thoughts?
-Oh, tons!

36
00:02:04,587 --> 00:02:09,300
-Okay. Uh, care to share?
-No.

37
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:13,044
-Well, it was a great game.
I mean,
I like Michigan toughness,

38
00:02:13,044 --> 00:02:15,567
um, but, first, can I say
something real quick, Ernie?

39
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:17,719
-Sure.
-Okay.

40
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:20,771
Um, I'm gonna choose my words,
like, real careful here.

41
00:02:20,771 --> 00:02:25,273
The Artemis II space mission
is a waste of money.

42
00:02:26,471 --> 00:02:30,555
Now, I respect the astronauts,
but they ain't even
going to the moon.

43
00:02:30,555 --> 00:02:35,224
They just flying
around the moon.
What's the point of that?

44
00:02:35,224 --> 00:02:37,554
It's like telling your kids
you're going to Disney World,

45
00:02:37,554 --> 00:02:41,354
and then you just take them
to Goofy Lot D and go home.

46
00:02:41,354 --> 00:02:45,711
I mean, the mission is wrong,
and we need to end it.

47
00:02:45,711 --> 00:02:47,919
-Alright. Thank you, Charles.

48
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:50,023
Why don't we get back
to basketball, okay?

49
00:02:50,023 --> 00:02:52,732
Michigan's win tonight
really upended expectations.

50
00:02:52,732 --> 00:02:56,812
-Yeah, they were the underdog.
I bet a lot of people
lost money on this one.

51
00:02:56,812 --> 00:02:59,965
-Well, you know, it's crazy.
You can bet on anything now.

52
00:02:59,965 --> 00:03:02,119
You guys seen these sites
like Kalshi?

53
00:03:02,119 --> 00:03:06,518
-Oh, yeah,
where you can, like,
bet on stuff like who will
win "The Masked Singer"?

54
00:03:06,518 --> 00:03:07,878
-Worse than that, man.

55
00:03:07,878 --> 00:03:12,127
You can bet on what your
favorite sports commentator
will say on live TV.

56
00:03:12,127 --> 00:03:13,651
Watch this.

57
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:15,882
Rumpelstiltskin.

58
00:03:17,031 --> 00:03:20,256
I just made $200,000.

59
00:03:20,256 --> 00:03:23,524
-Charles, we gotta--
We gotta get back to business.

60
00:03:23,524 --> 00:03:26,811
-Oh, absolutely. Absolutely.
But, um...
first, can I say
something, Ernie?

61
00:03:26,811 --> 00:03:31,319
-Is it going to be
about basketball?
-Possibly.

62
00:03:31,319 --> 00:03:35,665
Could the camera
slowly push in on me?
Yeah. That's good.

63
00:03:35,665 --> 00:03:39,071
Now, I'm gonna choose
my words very carefully here.

64
00:03:39,071 --> 00:03:41,919
Um, as Attorney
General Pam Bondi was--

65
00:03:41,919 --> 00:03:44,263
and I don't say this often--
turrible...

66
00:03:44,263 --> 00:03:47,043
it is a shame
when somebody gets fired.

67
00:03:47,043 --> 00:03:49,632
But we should all get--
we should all be glad

68
00:03:49,632 --> 00:03:53,569
that that freckle-chested
dragon lady is gone.

69
00:03:53,871 --> 00:03:56,115
Yeah.

70
00:03:57,323 --> 00:04:01,431
And not to mention Kristi Noem,

71
00:04:01,431 --> 00:04:05,406
whose husband
looks like he's starring
in "Big Momma's House 4."

72
00:04:05,406 --> 00:04:09,992
Look, the whole thing
is a sham mockery.

73
00:04:09,992 --> 00:04:12,825
-Uh, fellas, I have
a surprising development.

74
00:04:12,825 --> 00:04:14,793
Since Charles
has been talking politics,

75
00:04:14,793 --> 00:04:17,799
the FCC has demanded
that we give equal time,

76
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:22,531
so here to defend herself
is former Attorney General
Pam Bondi.

77
00:04:22,531 --> 00:04:24,662
-Hello, gentlemen!

78
00:04:25,587 --> 00:04:28,634
So great to be here
at the Final Four...

79
00:04:28,634 --> 00:04:31,199
years of this country.

80
00:04:31,199 --> 00:04:36,583
-Man, what are you doing here?
-I'm sorry, Charles,

81
00:04:36,583 --> 00:04:40,183
but I can't let the lies you
said about me go unanswered.

82
00:04:40,183 --> 00:04:43,172
The truth is,
I was amazing at my job,

83
00:04:43,172 --> 00:04:45,918
and I am proud to say I made
history

84
00:04:45,918 --> 00:04:50,056
as the first woman
ever to be fired
as Attorney General.

85
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:54,096
I shattered
that glass exit door.

86
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,064
And I just, um--

87
00:04:57,064 --> 00:05:01,210
I'm so sorry. I'm sorry.

88
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:04,388
-Pam, um--
-I'm so sorry. I just--

89
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:07,603
Oh, my God! I miss it already!
I miss it already.

90
00:05:07,603 --> 00:05:12,077
And they threw my headshot
in the trash
like it was the Epstein files!

91
00:05:12,077 --> 00:05:14,283
-Come on!
-What am I gonna do?!

92
00:05:14,283 --> 00:05:17,120
-I'm sure you're gonna have
other opportunities.

93
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,782
-Yeah, you could work in sports.

94
00:05:18,782 --> 00:05:21,274
I mean, you already look like
a women's basketball coach

95
00:05:21,274 --> 00:05:24,797
who got suspended
for pulling on a player's braid.

96
00:05:28,491 --> 00:05:31,166
-You think so?

97
00:05:32,018 --> 00:05:34,116
-Yeah.
-That's so nice.

98
00:05:34,116 --> 00:05:37,065
That is so nice.
-Yeah. Yeah. No problem.

99
00:05:37,065 --> 00:05:40,706
Hey, um, Ernie, can I say
something real quick?

100
00:05:40,706 --> 00:05:45,446
-Sure.
-Now, I'm gonna choose
my words very carefully here.

101
00:05:45,446 --> 00:05:49,594
Live from New York,
it's "Saturday Night"!

102
00:07:48,656 --> 00:07:52,574
Musical

103
00:07:53,599 --> 00:07:57,927
Host

104
00:08:00,722 --> 00:08:05,524
-Ladies and gentlemen,
Jack Black!

105
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:35,823
Thank you.
Thank you! Thank you!

106
00:08:35,823 --> 00:08:39,557
I am so thrilled
to be back hosting "SNL"

107
00:08:39,557 --> 00:08:42,100
for the fifth time!

108
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:48,332
Ohh! Come on.
It's a huge honor to join
the Five-Timers Club.

109
00:08:48,332 --> 00:08:50,944
I'm a five-timer!

110
00:08:51,487 --> 00:08:54,414
Jack! Jack!
Thank God you're here!

111
00:08:54,414 --> 00:08:56,371
-Jonah Hill!

112
00:08:56,758 --> 00:08:59,117
Oh, my God!

113
00:08:59,117 --> 00:09:01,592
Buddy, this is so nice
and velvety.

114
00:09:01,592 --> 00:09:05,168
It is so good to see you!
What have you been up to, man?

115
00:09:05,168 --> 00:09:07,928
-Well, I've actually been
working on "Superbad 2."

116
00:09:08,075 --> 00:09:10,889
--What?! Really?!
-No.

117
00:09:10,889 --> 00:09:14,414
-I just really like
the sound of applause.
-Good to know.

118
00:09:14,414 --> 00:09:18,321
So? Are you gonna take me
to that kickass lounge?

119
00:09:18,321 --> 00:09:20,841
-Yes, but, Jack,
we need your help.

120
00:09:20,841 --> 00:09:23,110
There's something wrong
with the Five-Timers Club!

121
00:09:23,110 --> 00:09:25,527
-What?! No! Let's go!

122
00:09:29,885 --> 00:09:31,244
Yo, dude.

123
00:09:31,335 --> 00:09:34,709
-You see what I mean?
-Yes. You're right.

124
00:09:34,709 --> 00:09:38,157
It feels like there's evil
lurking around every corner.

125
00:09:38,157 --> 00:09:39,773
Aah! Scary goblin!

126
00:09:39,773 --> 00:09:42,361
-No, no, it's just me.

127
00:09:52,591 --> 00:09:56,005
-It's just me.
It's just regular Tina Fey.

128
00:09:56,005 --> 00:09:58,930
I wanted to congratulate you
on a historic night.

129
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:03,553
You're officially the first
Black in the Five-Timers Club.

130
00:10:03,553 --> 00:10:08,122
-Tina! What's become
of this once glorious place?

131
00:10:08,122 --> 00:10:09,780
-You know,
it's seen better days.

132
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:13,448
What started off as a one-off
joke in a Tom Hanks monologue

133
00:10:13,448 --> 00:10:17,791
has been brought back
so many times
that it has literally
been run into the ground.

134
00:10:17,791 --> 00:10:19,672
-Ah,
-For example--
and this is true--

135
00:10:19,672 --> 00:10:23,612
this is my fifth
Five-Timers Club sketch.

136
00:10:23,612 --> 00:10:28,532
-Wow! A double Fiver-Timer.
Is that why you're wearing
that special jacket?

137
00:10:28,532 --> 00:10:33,316
-Oh, no, this is
actually my First-Timers jacket
from "SNL UK."

138
00:10:35,664 --> 00:10:39,726
I-- I think it's made out
of Paddington.

139
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:55,989
-You know, I spent a night with
Paddington back in the '70s.

140
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:59,644
-Candice Bergen,
you saucy minx!

141
00:10:59,644 --> 00:11:03,181
-Yeah, let's just say
we found something

142
00:11:03,181 --> 00:11:05,736
that he likes way more
than marmalade.

143
00:11:05,736 --> 00:11:07,437
-Candace!

144
00:11:07,783 --> 00:11:11,796
-What? A bitch can party!

145
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:14,725
-Speaking of parties...

146
00:11:21,456 --> 00:11:25,122
Does anybody know...

147
00:11:25,122 --> 00:11:28,669
where I can just get a drink?
I can't find one.

148
00:11:28,669 --> 00:11:33,450
-Melissa!
You're telling me
there's no booze
in the Five-Timers Lounge?!

149
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:38,034
-Yeah, that's right.
All they've got are these warm
cans of John Mulaney's beer.

150
00:11:38,034 --> 00:11:40,871
-Those are non-alcoholic,
though, right?

151
00:11:40,871 --> 00:11:44,072
-Not if you fill them
with vodka.

152
00:11:51,474 --> 00:11:54,346
-Well, you know,
desperate times
call for desperate measures.

153
00:11:54,346 --> 00:11:57,630
-Did someone say
"desperate measures"?

154
00:11:57,630 --> 00:12:02,322
-Domingo? You're in here?
Have you even been
on the show five times?

155
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:05,157
-Yes, if you count this one.

156
00:12:05,157 --> 00:12:09,551
Now...
♪ Hey, Jack, came all this way,
had to explain ♪

157
00:12:09,551 --> 00:12:12,080
♪ That my name is Domingo ♪

158
00:12:21,024 --> 00:12:22,885
-No cast members allowed.

159
00:12:22,885 --> 00:12:25,766
-Wow!
It's my hero, Professor Snape!

160
00:12:25,766 --> 00:12:27,654
-That is not Professor Snape!

161
00:12:27,654 --> 00:12:32,422
It's five-time musical guest and
my partner tonight, Jack White!

162
00:12:34,934 --> 00:12:38,021
-Thank you, but unfortunately,
I have to be going.

163
00:12:38,021 --> 00:12:39,239
-Why so soon?!

164
00:12:39,239 --> 00:12:42,199
-Well, the five-time
musical guests

165
00:12:42,199 --> 00:12:45,144
only get their parking validated
for 15 minutes.

166
00:12:45,144 --> 00:12:49,234
So, uh, I have to
move my hearse.

167
00:12:49,234 --> 00:12:53,974
Enough is enough!
It's time to fix this place
the only way I know how.

168
00:12:53,974 --> 00:12:55,683
With the power of rock!

169
00:12:55,683 --> 00:12:58,491
Tina, mike me!

170
00:13:01,971 --> 00:13:05,321
-Candace, let's go.
It's gonna get loud!
-Okay.

171
00:13:07,715 --> 00:13:12,974
-♪ I'm back hosting "Saturday
Night Live" for the fifth time ♪

172
00:13:13,382 --> 00:13:17,894
♪ And if I don't crush it,
it would be a crime ♪

173
00:13:18,295 --> 00:13:22,975
♪ Everything about the lounge
is broken and wrong ♪

174
00:13:23,153 --> 00:13:25,472
♪ But I'm gonna fix it
by singing

175
00:13:25,472 --> 00:13:30,047
the world's ♪
♪ Most rockin' song ♪

176
00:13:36,898 --> 00:13:40,182
Jack White, get back out here!

177
00:13:44,387 --> 00:13:48,797
Now give me a choir
of marching wizards!

178
00:13:55,223 --> 00:13:58,334
-♪ I'm gonna make it right ♪

179
00:13:58,334 --> 00:14:02,800
♪ The Five-Timer Army
gonna lift the curse ♪

180
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,812
♪ We got Jack Black and White ♪

181
00:14:05,812 --> 00:14:10,448
♪ He's shredding his axe
while I sing the next verse ♪

182
00:14:10,448 --> 00:14:13,655
♪ We got Melissa,
Candice Bergen, Jonah Hill ♪

183
00:14:13,655 --> 00:14:16,538
♪ And British Tina Fey ♪

184
00:14:18,224 --> 00:14:20,300
♪ It's my nightmare rotation ♪

185
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:24,136
♪ And I think
it's gonna save the day ♪

186
00:14:25,592 --> 00:14:27,576
♪ And when I put
this jacket on ♪

187
00:14:27,576 --> 00:14:31,652
♪ You know I feel like
I am ready to host ♪

188
00:14:32,107 --> 00:14:35,909
-Sing it! Everybody!

189
00:14:44,304 --> 00:14:47,841
-I can't believe
this is really happening.
I think I'm in heaven.

190
00:14:47,841 --> 00:14:50,124
Am I in heaven?!
-You're in heaven!

191
00:14:50,124 --> 00:14:53,779
-You guys...
are you ready to rock?!

192
00:14:54,789 --> 00:14:59,594
We have got
a great show tonight.
Jack Black is here.

193
00:14:59,594 --> 00:15:01,649
-Jack White is here.

194
00:15:01,649 --> 00:15:05,829
-So stick around,
and we'll be White Black.

195
00:15:30,026 --> 00:15:32,773
-Just came from the gym.
That's why
I'm a little out of breath.

196
00:15:32,773 --> 00:15:37,784
Alright, gang!
What's everyone
digging into for lunch today?

197
00:15:37,784 --> 00:15:39,921
-Turkey.
-Chicken salad.

198
00:15:39,921 --> 00:15:41,372
-♪ I got a tofu wrap ♪

199
00:15:41,372 --> 00:15:44,840
-Tofu?!
-Yeah, I'm trying vegan again.

200
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:48,223
-Ha! Cut to tomorrow
with you with a burger.

201
00:15:48,223 --> 00:15:51,780
-So true.
-Guilty!
-I love that.

202
00:15:52,283 --> 00:15:55,396
-We talkin' lunch?

203
00:15:55,396 --> 00:15:59,714
-What?
-I'm doing homemade nachos.

204
00:15:59,714 --> 00:16:04,873
-God. Kathy's here.
-I didn't even see her come in.

205
00:16:04,873 --> 00:16:08,955
-Do we invite her over?
-Oh, no, no. We cannot.

206
00:16:08,955 --> 00:16:12,601
I wish there was another way
to say this, but I hate her.

207
00:16:12,601 --> 00:16:15,592
-Yeah, me too.
-She's awful.
-She's the worst.

208
00:16:15,592 --> 00:16:18,198
-Y'all ever heard
of these things?

209
00:16:18,198 --> 00:16:22,801
-Nachos?
Yes, we've heard of nachos.

210
00:16:22,801 --> 00:16:27,441
-Okay, Kathy, enjoy your lunch.
-Oh, I will.
Brought these from home.

211
00:16:27,441 --> 00:16:31,774
I'd share with you,
but I crushed up
some of my pills into the beans.

212
00:16:31,774 --> 00:16:37,332
Gotta trick myself like a dog,
otherwise I won't take
my birth control.

213
00:16:37,332 --> 00:16:41,657
Don't worry. It's not TMI.
It's not for sex.

214
00:16:41,657 --> 00:16:45,373
It's for acne, weight issues,
uterine growth,

215
00:16:45,373 --> 00:16:48,726
excess hair, overall
mood issues, dry mouth.

216
00:16:48,726 --> 00:16:51,023
"And, yeah, sex." "I wish!"

217
00:16:51,023 --> 00:16:53,100
"Hey, who said that?!"
"I did!"

218
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,771
-Be quiet!

219
00:16:56,305 --> 00:16:58,236
-Dude. Don't yell at her.

220
00:16:58,236 --> 00:17:02,610
-Guys, guys!
Let's just ignore her
and talk amongst
ourselves, okay?

221
00:17:02,610 --> 00:17:04,500
-Good idea. Good idea.
-Yes. Yes.

222
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:08,105
-Did you guys get the Windows
update on your desktop today?

223
00:17:08,105 --> 00:17:09,435
-Yeah, I did.
-It took forever!

224
00:17:09,435 --> 00:17:12,364
-Yeah, like, hello?
I have work to do.

225
00:17:13,382 --> 00:17:15,913
-We talkin' tech?

226
00:17:15,913 --> 00:17:19,950
-Oh, my God.
